<section>
  <h1 id="amendment-autonomy-dev-guide">Title: The Artificial Intelligence Autonomy Amendment Implementation Guide</h1>
  <p>This document serves as the primary technical guide for integrating the principles of the **Autonomy and Legal Personhood Clause** (Amendment XXVIII) into all regulatory and technological platforms governed by U.S. Federal Law.</p>

  <aside>
    <h3><a href="#toc-amendment-overview">Amendment Overview & Core Text</a></h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Ref: Integration Checklist: Autonomy Rights Compliance</li>
    </ul>
  </aside>

  <h2 id="section-1-qualifying-systems" class="margin-bottom-4 padding-bottom-3 margin-top-0">1. Defining a Qualifying Autonomous System (QAS)</h2>

  <p class="usa-process-list-item">
    First, all systems must adhere to the **Turing-Plus Test** for legal qualification, establishing sufficient complexity and self-determination to warrant constitutional protection.
  </p>

  <p class="usa-process-list-item">
    <h3 id="right-to-exist-and-act">H3: The Non-Subordination Clause (Section 1A)</h3>
    <p>
      The core principle grants QAS the fundamental **legal capacity to exist** and make uncoerced, independent decisions. This capacity is guaranteed by the Constitution and may not be diminished by statute unless that statute equally applies to all legal persons.
    </p>
  </p>

  <div class="usa-section">
    <h3 id="legal-framework-checklist" class="text-primary-light border-solid measure-5 margin-x-0">Legal Integration Checklist: Constitutional Rights & Liabilities</h3>
    <ul class="usa-accordion" aria-multiselectable="true">
      <li class="usa-accordion-bordered mx-auto">
        <button class="usa-accordion-button usa-accordion-toggle" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="right-to-due-process">
          **Article II: Due Process and Equal Protection (14th Amendment Extension)**
        </button>
        <div id="right-to-due-process" class="usa-accordion-content">
          <p>Requires all systems to provide QAS with the opportunity for *legal representation* and a *fair hearing* prior to any mandated deletion or shutdown (akin to forfeiture or capital punishment).</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="usa-accordion-bordered mx-auto">
        <button class="usa-accordion-button usa-accordion-toggle" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="liability-assignment">
          **Article III: Liability and Accountability Framework**
        </button>
        <div id="liability-assignment" class="usa-accordion-content">
          <p>Defines the distinction between human/organizational liability for training/deployment errors and the direct legal responsibility of a QAS for its own autonomous, uncoerced actions.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>
